	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Repro steps:&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game&#xD;&#xA;2. loadlevel WLD_Main_A&#xD;&#xA;3. oe qnight NIGHT_OwlbearCub2_5cc6fbd5-0b70-4fb5-a29c-9b7ed9e39fcc&#xD;&#xA;4. End the day and go to camp&#xD;&#xA;5. Go to sleep, the dialog will start" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="1373" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="IMPROTANT: If players help the cub in this dialog, it becomes the permamement camp follower.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;In SwA, the owlbear cub speaks in short staccato 'sentences.' He's vicious and feral - but scared. He's slightly injured, and playing it up more than it is, and he's distrustful of the player at first. If the player helps him, he becomes excited and runs off to hunt. In the next night, he returns with a dead bird.&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;The owlbear has appeared in camp for a second night.  The player has previously spared the cub after killing its mother, and saved it from a cruel game run by the goblins in their camp.&#xA;He reacts much more suspiciously of the player if they antagonised him in their first encounter.&#xA;" />
			<children>
				<node id="defaultAttitudes">
